34 CConfig::CConfig(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE], unsigned short val_software, unsigned short val_iZone, unsigned short val_nZone, unsigned short val_nDim, unsigned short verb_level) {
35 
36  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
37 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
38  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
39 #endif
40 
41  /*--- Initialize pointers to Null---*/
42 
43  SetPointersNull();
44 
45  /*--- Reading config options ---*/
46 
47  SetConfig_Options(val_iZone, val_nZone);
48 
49  /*--- Parsing the config file ---*/
50 
51  SetConfig_Parsing(case_filename);
52 
53  /*--- Configuration file postprocessing ---*/
54 
55  SetPostprocessing(val_software, val_iZone, val_nDim);
56 
57  /*--- Configuration file boundaries/markers setting ---*/
58 
59  SetMarkers(val_software);
60 
61  /*--- Configuration file output ---*/
62 
63  if ((rank == MASTER_NODE) && (verb_level == VERB_HIGH) && (val_iZone != 1))
64  SetOutput(val_software, val_iZone);
65 
66 }

88 CConfig::CConfig(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE], CConfig *config) {
89 
90  bool runtime_file = false;
91 
92  /*--- Initialize pointers to Null---*/
93 
94  SetPointersNull();
95 
96  /*--- Reading config options ---*/
97 
98  SetRunTime_Options();
99 
100  /*--- Parsing the config file ---*/
101 
102  runtime_file = SetRunTime_Parsing(case_filename);
103 
104  /*--- Update original config file ---*/

222  // This config file is parsed by a number of programs to make it easy to write SU2
223  // wrapper scripts (in python, go, etc.) so please do

226  // play nice with the existing format so that you don't break the existing scripts.

1566 void CConfig::SetConfig_Parsing(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE]) {
1567  string text_line, option_name;
1568  ifstream case_file;
1569  vector<string> option_value;
1570  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
1571 
1572 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1573  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
1574 #endif
1575 
1576  /*--- Read the configuration file ---*/
1577 
1578  case_file.open(case_filename, ios::in);
1579 
1580  if (case_file.fail()) {
1581  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << endl << "The configuration file (.cfg) is missing!!" << endl << endl;
1582  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1583  }
1584 
1585  string errorString;
1586 
1587  int err_count = 0; // How many errors have we found in the config file
1588  int max_err_count = 30; // Maximum number of errors to print before stopping
1589 
1590  map<string, bool> included_options;
1591 
1592  /*--- Parse the configuration file and set the options ---*/
1593 
1594  while (getline (case_file, text_line)) {
1595 
1596  if (err_count >= max_err_count) {
1597  errorString.append("too many errors. Stopping parse");
1598 
1599  cout << errorString << endl;
1600  throw(1);
1601  }
1602 
1603  if (TokenizeString(text_line, option_name, option_value)) {
1604 
1605  /*--- See if it's a python option ---*/
1606 
1607  if (option_map.find(option_name) == option_map.end()) {
1608  string newString;
1609  newString.append(option_name);
1610  newString.append(": invalid option name");
1611  newString.append(". Check current SU2 options in config_template.cfg.");
1612  newString.append("\n");
1613  errorString.append(newString);
1614  err_count++;
1615  continue;
1616  }
1617 
1618  /*--- Option exists, check if the option has already been in the config file ---*/
1619 
1620  if (included_options.find(option_name) != included_options.end()) {
1621  string newString;
1622  newString.append(option_name);
1623  newString.append(": option appears twice");
1624  newString.append("\n");
1625  errorString.append(newString);
1626  err_count++;
1627  continue;
1628  }
1629 
1630 
1631  /*--- New found option. Add it to the map, and delete from all options ---*/
1632 
1633  included_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(option_name, true));
1634  all_options.erase(option_name);
1635 
1636  /*--- Set the value and check error ---*/
1637 
1638  string out = option_map[option_name]->SetValue(option_value);
1639  if (out.compare("") != 0) {
1640  errorString.append(out);
1641  errorString.append("\n");
1642  err_count++;
1643  }
1644  }
1645  }
1646 
1647  /*--- See if there were any errors parsing the config file ---*/
1648 
1649  if (errorString.size() != 0) {
1650  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << errorString << endl;
1651  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1652  }
1653 
1654  /*--- Set the default values for all of the options that weren't set ---*/
1655 
1656  for (map<string, bool>::iterator iter = all_options.begin(); iter != all_options.end(); ++iter) {
1657  option_map[iter->first]->SetDefault();
1658  }
1659 
1660  case_file.close();
1661 
1662 }
1663 
1664 bool CConfig::SetRunTime_Parsing(char case_filename[MAX_STRING_SIZE]) {
1665  string text_line, option_name;
1666  ifstream case_file;
1667  vector<string> option_value;
1668  int rank = MASTER_NODE;
1669 
1670 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1671  MPI_Comm_rank(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &rank);
1672 #endif
1673 
1674  /*--- Read the configuration file ---*/
1675 
1676  case_file.open(case_filename, ios::in);
1677 
1678  if (case_file.fail()) { return false; }
1679 
1680  string errorString;
1681 
1682  int err_count = 0; // How many errors have we found in the config file
1683  int max_err_count = 30; // Maximum number of errors to print before stopping
1684 
1685  map<string, bool> included_options;
1686 
1687  /*--- Parse the configuration file and set the options ---*/
1688 
1689  while (getline (case_file, text_line)) {
1690 
1691  if (err_count >= max_err_count) {
1692  errorString.append("too many errors. Stopping parse");
1693 
1694  cout << errorString << endl;
1695  throw(1);
1696  }
1697 
1698  if (TokenizeString(text_line, option_name, option_value)) {
1699 
1700  if (option_map.find(option_name) == option_map.end()) {
1701 
1702  /*--- See if it's a python option ---*/
1703 
1704  string newString;
1705  newString.append(option_name);
1706  newString.append(": invalid option name");
1707  newString.append("\n");
1708  errorString.append(newString);
1709  err_count++;
1710  continue;
1711  }
1712 
1713  /*--- Option exists, check if the option has already been in the config file ---*/
1714 
1715  if (included_options.find(option_name) != included_options.end()) {
1716  string newString;
1717  newString.append(option_name);
1718  newString.append(": option appears twice");
1719  newString.append("\n");
1720  errorString.append(newString);
1721  err_count++;
1722  continue;
1723  }
1724 
1725  /*--- New found option. Add it to the map, and delete from all options ---*/
1726 
1727  included_options.insert(pair<string, bool>(option_name, true));
1728  all_options.erase(option_name);
1729 
1730  /*--- Set the value and check error ---*/
1731 
1732  string out = option_map[option_name]->SetValue(option_value);
1733  if (out.compare("") != 0) {
1734  errorString.append(out);
1735  errorString.append("\n");
1736  err_count++;
1737  }
1738 
1739  }
1740  }
1741 
1742  /*--- See if there were any errors parsing the runtime file ---*/
1743 
1744  if (errorString.size() != 0) {
1745  if (rank == MASTER_NODE) cout << errorString << endl;
1746  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1747  }
1748 
1749  case_file.close();
1750 
1751  return true;
1752 
1753 }
1754 
1755 void CConfig::SetPostprocessing(unsigned short val_software, unsigned short val_izone, unsigned short val_nDim) {
1756 
1757  unsigned short iZone, iCFL, iDim;
1758  bool ideal_gas = (Kind_FluidModel == STANDARD_AIR || Kind_FluidModel == IDEAL_GAS );
1759  bool standard_air = (Kind_FluidModel == STANDARD_AIR);
1760 
1761 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
1762  int size = SINGLE_NODE;
1763  MPI_Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &size);
1764 #endif
1765 
1766 #ifndef HAVE_TECIO
1767  if (Output_FileFormat == TECPLOT_BINARY) {
1768  cout << "Tecplot binary file requested but SU2 was built without TecIO support." << "\n";
1769  Output_FileFormat = TECPLOT;
1770  }
1771 #endif
1772 
1773  /*--- Store the SU2 module that we are executing. ---*/
1774 
1775  Kind_SU2 = val_software;
1776 
1777  /*--- Make sure that 1D outputs are written when objective function requires ---*/
1778 
1779  if (Kind_ObjFunc== AVG_OUTLET_PRESSURE || Kind_ObjFunc == AVG_TOTAL_PRESSURE || Kind_ObjFunc == OUTFLOW_GENERALIZED) {
1780  Wrt_1D_Output = YES;
1781  Marker_Out_1D = new string[nMarker_Monitoring];
1782  for (unsigned short iMarker=0; iMarker<nMarker_Monitoring; iMarker++){
1783  Marker_Out_1D[iMarker] = Marker_Monitoring[iMarker];
1784  }
1785  nMarker_Out_1D = nMarker_Monitoring;
1786  }
1787

1789 
1790  if (Output_FileFormat != TECPLOT) Low_MemoryOutput = NO;
1791 
1792  /*--- Deactivate the multigrid in the adjoint problem ---*/
1793 
1794  if ((ContinuousAdjoint && !MG_AdjointFlow) ||
1795  (Unsteady_Simulation == TIME_STEPPING)) { nMGLevels = 0; }
1796 
1797  /*--- If Fluid Structure Interaction, set the solver for each zone.
1798  *--- ZONE_0 is the zone of the fluid.
1799  *--- All the other zones are structure.
1800  *--- This will allow us to define multiple physics structural problems */
1801 
1802  if (Kind_Solver == FLUID_STRUCTURE_INTERACTION){
1803  if (val_izone==0) { Kind_Solver = Kind_Solver_Fluid_FSI; FSI_Problem = true;}
1804 
1805  else { Kind_Solver = Kind_Solver_Struc_FSI; FSI_Problem = true;
1806  Kind_Linear_Solver = Kind_Linear_Solver_FSI_Struc;
1807  Kind_Linear_Solver_Prec = Kind_Linear_Solver_Prec_FSI_Struc;
1808  Linear_Solver_Error = Linear_Solver_Error_FSI_Struc;
1809  Linear_Solver_Iter = Linear_Solver_Iter_FSI_Struc;}
1810  }
1811  else{ FSI_Problem = false; }
1812

1815 
1816  Nonphys_Points = 0;
1817  Nonphys_Reconstr = 0;
1818 
1819  /*--- Don't do any deformation if there is no Design variable information ---*/
1820 
1821  if (Design_Variable == NULL) {
1822  Design_Variable = new unsigned short [1];
1823  nDV = 1; Design_Variable[0] = NONE;
1824  }
1825 
1826  /*--- Identification of free-surface problem, this problems are always
1827  unsteady and incompressible. ---*/
1828 
1829  if (Kind_Regime == FREESURFACE) {
1830  if (Unsteady_Simulation != DT_STEPPING_2ND) Unsteady_Simulation = DT_STEPPING_1ST;
1831  }
1832 
1833  if (Kind_Solver == POISSON_EQUATION) {
1834  Unsteady_Simulation = STEADY;
1835  }
1836 
1837  /*--- Set the number of external iterations to 1 for the steady state problem ---*/
1838 
1839  if ((Kind_Solver == HEAT_EQUATION) ||
1840  (Kind_Solver == WAVE_EQUATION) || (Kind_Solver == POISSON_EQUATION)) {
1841  nMGLevels = 0;
1842  if (Unsteady_Simulation == STEADY) nExtIter = 1;
1843  else Unst_nIntIter = 2;
1844  }
1845 
1846  if (Kind_Solver == FEM_ELASTICITY) {
1847  nMGLevels = 0;
1848  if (Dynamic_Analysis == STATIC)
1849  nExtIter = 1;
1850  }
1851 
1852  /*--- Decide whether we should be writing unsteady solution files. ---*/
1853 
1854  if (Unsteady_Simulation == STEADY ||
1855  Unsteady_Simulation == TIME_SPECTRAL ||
1856  Kind_Regime == FREESURFACE) { Wrt_Unsteady = false; }
1857  else { Wrt_Unsteady = true; }
1858 
1859  if (Kind_Solver == FEM_ELASTICITY) {
1860 
1861  if (Dynamic_Analysis == STATIC) { Wrt_Dynamic = false; }
1862  else { Wrt_Dynamic = true; }
1863 
1864  } else {
1865  Wrt_Dynamic = false;
1866  }
1867 
1868 
1869  /*--- Check for Fluid model consistency ---*/
1870 
1871  if (standard_air){
1872  if (Gamma != 1.4 || Gas_Constant != 287.058){
1873  Gamma = 1.4;
1874  Gas_Constant = 287.058;
1875  }
1876  }
1877  /*--- Check for Measurement System ---*/
1878 
1879  if (SystemMeasurements == US && !standard_air) {
1880  cout << "Only STANDARD_AIR fluid model can be used with US Measurement System" << endl;
1881  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1882  }
1883 
1884  /*--- Check for Convective scheme available for NICFD ---*/
1885

1888  cout << "Only ROE Upwind and HLLC Upwind scheme can be used for Non-Ideal Compressible Fluids" << endl;
1889  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1890  }
1891  else {
1892  if (Kind_Upwind_Flow != ROE && Kind_Upwind_Flow != HLLC) {
1893  cout << "Only ROE Upwind and HLLC Upwind scheme can be used for Non-Ideal Compressible Fluids" << endl;
1894  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1895  }
1896  }

1904  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1905  }
1906  if (nMarker_Outlet != 0) {

1908  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);

1914  }
1915

1924  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
1925  }
1926  }

1934  /*--- Set grid movement kind to NO_MOVEMENT if not specified, which means

1939  Kind_GridMovement = new unsigned short[nZone];
1940  for (unsigned short iZone = 0; iZone < nZone; iZone++ )

1942  if (Grid_Movement == true) {

1944  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);

1969  else

2295  /*--- Use the various rigid-motion input frequencies to determine the period to be used with time-spectral cases.
2296  There are THREE types of motion to consider, namely: rotation, pitching, and plunging.
2297  The largest period of motion is the one to be used for time-spectral calculations. ---*/
2298 
2299  if (Unsteady_Simulation == TIME_SPECTRAL) {
2300 
2301  unsigned short N_MOTION_TYPES = 3;
2302  su2double *periods;
2303  periods = new su2double[N_MOTION_TYPES];
2304 
2305  /*--- rotation: ---*/
2306 
2307  su2double Omega_mag_rot = sqrt(pow(Rotation_Rate_X[ZONE_0],2)+pow(Rotation_Rate_Y[ZONE_0],2)+pow(Rotation_Rate_Z[ZONE_0],2));
2308  if (Omega_mag_rot > 0)
2309  periods[0] = 2*PI_NUMBER/Omega_mag_rot;
2310  else
2311  periods[0] = 0.0;
2312 
2313  /*--- pitching: ---*/
2314 
2315  su2double Omega_mag_pitch = sqrt(pow(Pitching_Omega_X[ZONE_0],2)+pow(Pitching_Omega_Y[ZONE_0],2)+pow(Pitching_Omega_Z[ZONE_0],2));
2316  if (Omega_mag_pitch > 0)
2317  periods[1] = 2*PI_NUMBER/Omega_mag_pitch;
2318  else
2319  periods[1] = 0.0;
2320 
2321  /*--- plunging: ---*/
2322 
2323  su2double Omega_mag_plunge = sqrt(pow(Plunging_Omega_X[ZONE_0],2)+pow(Plunging_Omega_Y[ZONE_0],2)+pow(Plunging_Omega_Z[ZONE_0],2));
2324  if (Omega_mag_plunge > 0)
2325  periods[2] = 2*PI_NUMBER/Omega_mag_plunge;
2326  else
2327  periods[2] = 0.0;
2328 
2329  /*--- determine which period is largest ---*/
2330 
2331  unsigned short iVar;
2332  TimeSpectral_Period = 0.0;
2333  for (iVar = 0; iVar < N_MOTION_TYPES; iVar++) {
2334  if (periods[iVar] > TimeSpectral_Period)
2335  TimeSpectral_Period = periods[iVar];
2336  }
2337 
2338  delete periods;
2339 
2340  }
2341 
2342  /*--- Initialize the RefOriginMoment Pointer ---*/
2343 
2344  RefOriginMoment = NULL;
2345  RefOriginMoment = new su2double[3];
2346  RefOriginMoment[0] = 0.0; RefOriginMoment[1] = 0.0; RefOriginMoment[2] = 0.0;
2347 
2348  /*--- In case the moment origin coordinates have not been declared in the
2349  config file, set them equal to zero for safety. Also check to make sure
2350  that for each marker, a value has been declared for the moment origin.
2351  Unless only one value was specified, then set this value for all the markers
2352  being monitored. ---*/
2353 
2354  unsigned short iMarker;
2355 
2356  if ((nRefOriginMoment_X != nRefOriginMoment_Y) || (nRefOriginMoment_X != nRefOriginMoment_Z) ) {
2357  cout << "ERROR: Length of REF_ORIGIN_MOMENT_X, REF_ORIGIN_MOMENT_Y and REF_ORIGIN_MOMENT_Z must be the same!!" << endl;
2358  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
2359  }
2360 
2361  if (RefOriginMoment_X == NULL) {
2362  RefOriginMoment_X = new su2double[nMarker_Monitoring];
2363  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Monitoring; iMarker++ )
2364  RefOriginMoment_X[iMarker] = 0.0;
2365  } else {
2366  if (nRefOriginMoment_X == 1) {
2367 
2368  su2double aux_RefOriginMoment_X = RefOriginMoment_X[0];
2369  delete [] RefOriginMoment_X;
2370  RefOriginMoment_X = new su2double[nMarker_Monitoring];
2371  nRefOriginMoment_X = nMarker_Monitoring;
2372 
2373  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Monitoring; iMarker++ )
2374  RefOriginMoment_X[iMarker] = aux_RefOriginMoment_X;
2375  }
2376  else if (nRefOriginMoment_X != nMarker_Monitoring) {
2377  cout << "ERROR: Length of REF_ORIGIN_MOMENT_X must match number of Monitoring Markers!!" << endl;
2378  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
2379  }
2380  }
2381 
2382  if (RefOriginMoment_Y == NULL) {
2383  RefOriginMoment_Y = new su2double[nMarker_Monitoring];
2384  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Monitoring; iMarker++ )
2385  RefOriginMoment_Y[iMarker] = 0.0;
2386  } else {
2387  if (nRefOriginMoment_Y == 1) {
2388 
2389  su2double aux_RefOriginMoment_Y = RefOriginMoment_Y[0];
2390  delete [] RefOriginMoment_Y;
2391  RefOriginMoment_Y = new su2double[nMarker_Monitoring];
2392  nRefOriginMoment_Y = nMarker_Monitoring;
2393 
2394  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Monitoring; iMarker++ )
2395  RefOriginMoment_Y[iMarker] = aux_RefOriginMoment_Y;
2396  }
2397  else if (nRefOriginMoment_Y != nMarker_Monitoring) {
2398  cout << "ERROR: Length of REF_ORIGIN_MOMENT_Y must match number of Monitoring Markers!!" << endl;
2399  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
2400  }
2401  }
2402 
2403  if (RefOriginMoment_Z == NULL) {
2404  RefOriginMoment_Z = new su2double[nMarker_Monitoring];
2405  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Monitoring; iMarker++ )
2406  RefOriginMoment_Z[iMarker] = 0.0;
2407  } else {
2408  if (nRefOriginMoment_Z == 1) {
2409 
2410  su2double aux_RefOriginMoment_Z = RefOriginMoment_Z[0];
2411  delete [] RefOriginMoment_Z;
2412  RefOriginMoment_Z = new su2double[nMarker_Monitoring];
2413  nRefOriginMoment_Z = nMarker_Monitoring;
2414 
2415  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Monitoring; iMarker++ )
2416  RefOriginMoment_Z[iMarker] = aux_RefOriginMoment_Z;
2417  }
2418  else if (nRefOriginMoment_Z != nMarker_Monitoring) {
2419  cout << "ERROR: Length of REF_ORIGIN_MOMENT_Z must match number of Monitoring Markers!!" << endl;
2420  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
2421  }
2422  }
2423 
2424  /*--- Set the boolean flag if we are carrying out an aeroelastic simulation. ---*/
2425 
2426  if (Grid_Movement && (Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] == AEROELASTIC || Kind_GridMovement[ZONE_0] == AEROELASTIC_RIGID_MOTION)) Aeroelastic_Simulation = true;
2427  else Aeroelastic_Simulation = false;
2428 
2429  /*--- Initializing the size for the solutions of the Aeroelastic problem. ---*/
2430 
2431 
2432  if (Grid_Movement && Aeroelastic_Simulation) {
2433  Aeroelastic_np1.resize(nMarker_Monitoring);
2434  Aeroelastic_n.resize(nMarker_Monitoring);
2435  Aeroelastic_n1.resize(nMarker_Monitoring);
2436  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Monitoring; iMarker++) {
2437  Aeroelastic_np1[iMarker].resize(2);
2438  Aeroelastic_n[iMarker].resize(2);
2439  Aeroelastic_n1[iMarker].resize(2);
2440  for (int i =0; i<2; i++) {
2441  Aeroelastic_np1[iMarker][i].resize(2);
2442  Aeroelastic_n[iMarker][i].resize(2);
2443  Aeroelastic_n1[iMarker][i].resize(2);
2444  for (int j=0; j<2; j++) {
2445  Aeroelastic_np1[iMarker][i][j] = 0.0;
2446  Aeroelastic_n[iMarker][i][j] = 0.0;
2447  Aeroelastic_n1[iMarker][i][j] = 0.0;
2448  }
2449  }
2450  }
2451  }
2452 
2453  /*--- Allocate memory for the plunge and pitch and initialized them to zero ---*/
2454 
2455  if (Grid_Movement && Aeroelastic_Simulation) {
2456  Aeroelastic_pitch = new su2double[nMarker_Monitoring];
2457  Aeroelastic_plunge = new su2double[nMarker_Monitoring];
2458  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Monitoring; iMarker++ ) {
2459  Aeroelastic_pitch[iMarker] = 0.0;
2460  Aeroelastic_plunge[iMarker] = 0.0;
2461  }
2462  }
2463 
2464  /*--- Fluid-Structure Interaction problems ---*/
2465 
2466  if (FSI_Problem) {
2467  Kind_GridMovement[val_izone] = FLUID_STRUCTURE;
2468  Grid_Movement = true;
2469  }
2470 
2471  if (MGCycle == FULLMG_CYCLE) FinestMesh = nMGLevels;
2472  else FinestMesh = MESH_0;
2473 
2474  if ((Kind_Solver == NAVIER_STOKES) &&
2475  (Kind_Turb_Model != NONE))
2476  Kind_Solver = RANS;
2477 
2478  if (Kind_Regime == FREESURFACE) GravityForce = true;
2479 
2480  Kappa_1st_Flow = Kappa_Flow[0];
2481  Kappa_2nd_Flow = Kappa_Flow[1];
2482  Kappa_4th_Flow = Kappa_Flow[2];
2483  Kappa_1st_AdjFlow = Kappa_AdjFlow[0];
2484  Kappa_2nd_AdjFlow = Kappa_AdjFlow[1];
2485  Kappa_4th_AdjFlow = Kappa_AdjFlow[2];
2486 
2487  /*--- Make the MG_PreSmooth, MG_PostSmooth, and MG_CorrecSmooth
2488  arrays consistent with nMGLevels ---*/
2489 
2490  unsigned short * tmp_smooth = new unsigned short[nMGLevels+1];
2491 
2492  if ((nMG_PreSmooth != nMGLevels+1) && (nMG_PreSmooth != 0)) {
2493  if (nMG_PreSmooth > nMGLevels+1) {
2494 
2495  /*--- Truncate by removing unnecessary elements at the end ---*/
2496 
2497  for (unsigned int i = 0; i <= nMGLevels; i++)
2498  tmp_smooth[i] = MG_PreSmooth[i];
2499  delete [] MG_PreSmooth;
2500  MG_PreSmooth=NULL;
2501  } else {
2502 
2503  /*--- Add additional elements equal to last element ---*/
2504 
2505  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < nMG_PreSmooth; i++)
2506  tmp_smooth[i] = MG_PreSmooth[i];
2507  for (unsigned int i = nMG_PreSmooth; i <= nMGLevels; i++)
2508  tmp_smooth[i] = MG_PreSmooth[nMG_PreSmooth-1];
2509  delete [] MG_PreSmooth;
2510  MG_PreSmooth=NULL;
2511  }
2512 
2513  nMG_PreSmooth = nMGLevels+1;
2514  MG_PreSmooth = new unsigned short[nMG_PreSmooth];
2515  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < nMG_PreSmooth; i++)
2516  MG_PreSmooth[i] = tmp_smooth[i];
2517  }
2518  if ((nMGLevels != 0) && (nMG_PreSmooth == 0)) {
2519  delete [] MG_PreSmooth;
2520  nMG_PreSmooth = nMGLevels+1;
2521  MG_PreSmooth = new unsigned short[nMG_PreSmooth];
2522  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < nMG_PreSmooth; i++)
2523  MG_PreSmooth[i] = i+1;
2524  }
2525 
2526  if ((nMG_PostSmooth != nMGLevels+1) && (nMG_PostSmooth != 0)) {
2527  if (nMG_PostSmooth > nMGLevels+1) {
2528 
2529  /*--- Truncate by removing unnecessary elements at the end ---*/
2530 
2531  for (unsigned int i = 0; i <= nMGLevels; i++)
2532  tmp_smooth[i] = MG_PostSmooth[i];
2533  delete [] MG_PostSmooth;
2534  MG_PostSmooth=NULL;
2535  } else {
2536 
2537  /*--- Add additional elements equal to last element ---*/
2538 
2539  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < nMG_PostSmooth; i++)
2540  tmp_smooth[i] = MG_PostSmooth[i];
2541  for (unsigned int i = nMG_PostSmooth; i <= nMGLevels; i++)
2542  tmp_smooth[i] = MG_PostSmooth[nMG_PostSmooth-1];
2543  delete [] MG_PostSmooth;
2544  MG_PostSmooth=NULL;
2545  }
2546 
2547  nMG_PostSmooth = nMGLevels+1;
2548  MG_PostSmooth = new unsigned short[nMG_PostSmooth];
2549  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < nMG_PostSmooth; i++)
2550  MG_PostSmooth[i] = tmp_smooth[i];
2551 
2552  }
2553 
2554  if ((nMGLevels != 0) && (nMG_PostSmooth == 0)) {
2555  delete [] MG_PostSmooth;
2556  nMG_PostSmooth = nMGLevels+1;
2557  MG_PostSmooth = new unsigned short[nMG_PostSmooth];
2558  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < nMG_PostSmooth; i++)
2559  MG_PostSmooth[i] = 0;
2560  }
2561 
2562  if ((nMG_CorrecSmooth != nMGLevels+1) && (nMG_CorrecSmooth != 0)) {
2563  if (nMG_CorrecSmooth > nMGLevels+1) {
2564 
2565  /*--- Truncate by removing unnecessary elements at the end ---*/
2566 
2567  for (unsigned int i = 0; i <= nMGLevels; i++)
2568  tmp_smooth[i] = MG_CorrecSmooth[i];
2569  delete [] MG_CorrecSmooth;
2570  MG_CorrecSmooth = NULL;
2571  } else {
2572 
2573  /*--- Add additional elements equal to last element ---*/
2574 
2575  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < nMG_CorrecSmooth; i++)
2576  tmp_smooth[i] = MG_CorrecSmooth[i];
2577  for (unsigned int i = nMG_CorrecSmooth; i <= nMGLevels; i++)
2578  tmp_smooth[i] = MG_CorrecSmooth[nMG_CorrecSmooth-1];
2579  delete [] MG_CorrecSmooth;
2580  MG_CorrecSmooth = NULL;
2581  }
2582  nMG_CorrecSmooth = nMGLevels+1;
2583  MG_CorrecSmooth = new unsigned short[nMG_CorrecSmooth];
2584  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < nMG_CorrecSmooth; i++)
2585  MG_CorrecSmooth[i] = tmp_smooth[i];
2586  }
2587 
2588  if ((nMGLevels != 0) && (nMG_CorrecSmooth == 0)) {
2589  delete [] MG_CorrecSmooth;
2590  nMG_CorrecSmooth = nMGLevels+1;
2591  MG_CorrecSmooth = new unsigned short[nMG_CorrecSmooth];
2592  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < nMG_CorrecSmooth; i++)
2593  MG_CorrecSmooth[i] = 0;
2594  }
2595 
2596  /*--- Override MG Smooth parameters ---*/
2597 
2598  if (nMG_PreSmooth != 0) MG_PreSmooth[MESH_0] = 1;
2599  if (nMG_PostSmooth != 0) {
2600  MG_PostSmooth[MESH_0] = 0;
2601  MG_PostSmooth[nMGLevels] = 0;
2602  }
2603  if (nMG_CorrecSmooth != 0) MG_CorrecSmooth[nMGLevels] = 0;
2604 
2605  if (Restart) MGCycle = V_CYCLE;
2606 
2607  if (ContinuousAdjoint) {
2608  if (Kind_Solver == EULER) Kind_Solver = ADJ_EULER;
2609  if (Kind_Solver == NAVIER_STOKES) Kind_Solver = ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES;
2610  if (Kind_Solver == RANS) Kind_Solver = ADJ_RANS;
2611  }
2612 
2613  nCFL = nMGLevels+1;
2614  CFL = new su2double[nCFL];
2615  CFL[0] = CFLFineGrid;
2616  if (ContinuousAdjoint){
2617  CFL[0] = CFL[0] * CFLRedCoeff_AdjFlow;
2618  CFL_AdaptParam[2]*=CFLRedCoeff_AdjFlow;
2619  CFL_AdaptParam[3]*=CFLRedCoeff_AdjFlow;
2620  }
2621 
2622  for (iCFL = 1; iCFL < nCFL; iCFL++)
2623  CFL[iCFL] = CFL[iCFL-1];
2624 
2625  if (nRKStep == 0) {
2626  nRKStep = 1;
2627  RK_Alpha_Step = new su2double[1]; RK_Alpha_Step[0] = 1.0;
2628  }
2629 
2630  if (nIntCoeffs == 0) {
2631  nIntCoeffs = 2;
2632  Int_Coeffs = new su2double[2]; Int_Coeffs[0] = 0.25; Int_Coeffs[1] = 0.5;
2633  }
2634 
2635  if ((Kind_SU2 == SU2_CFD) && (Kind_Solver == NO_SOLVER)) {
2636  cout << "PHYSICAL_PROBLEM must be set in the configuration file" << endl;
2637  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
2638  }
2639 
2640  /*--- Set a flag for viscous simulations ---*/
2641 
2642  Viscous = (( Kind_Solver == NAVIER_STOKES ) ||
2643  ( Kind_Solver == ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES ) ||
2644  ( Kind_Solver == RANS ) ||
2645  ( Kind_Solver == ADJ_RANS ) );
2646 
2647 
2648  /*--- Re-scale the length based parameters. The US system uses feet,
2649  but SU2 assumes that the grid is in inches ---*/
2650 
2651  if ((SystemMeasurements == US) && (Kind_SU2 == SU2_CFD)) {
2652 
2653  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_Monitoring; iMarker++) {
2654  RefOriginMoment_X[iMarker] = RefOriginMoment_X[iMarker]/12.0;
2655  RefOriginMoment_Y[iMarker] = RefOriginMoment_Y[iMarker]/12.0;
2656  RefOriginMoment_Z[iMarker] = RefOriginMoment_Z[iMarker]/12.0;
2657  }
2658 
2659  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nGridMovement; iMarker++) {
2660  Motion_Origin_X[iMarker] = Motion_Origin_X[iMarker]/12.0;
2661  Motion_Origin_Y[iMarker] = Motion_Origin_Y[iMarker]/12.0;
2662  Motion_Origin_Z[iMarker] = Motion_Origin_Z[iMarker]/12.0;
2663  }
2664 
2665  RefLengthMoment = RefLengthMoment/12.0;
2666  if (val_nDim == 2) RefAreaCoeff = RefAreaCoeff/12.0;
2667  else RefAreaCoeff = RefAreaCoeff/144.0;
2668  Length_Reynolds = Length_Reynolds/12.0;
2669  RefElemLength = RefElemLength/12.0;
2670 
2671  EA_IntLimit[0] = EA_IntLimit[0]/12.0;
2672  EA_IntLimit[1] = EA_IntLimit[1]/12.0;
2673  EA_IntLimit[2] = EA_IntLimit[2]/12.0;
2674 
2675  Section_Location[0] = Section_Location[0]/12.0;
2676  Section_Location[1] = Section_Location[1]/12.0;
2677 
2678  Subsonic_Engine_Box[0] = Subsonic_Engine_Box[0]/12.0;
2679  Subsonic_Engine_Box[1] = Subsonic_Engine_Box[1]/12.0;
2680  Subsonic_Engine_Box[2] = Subsonic_Engine_Box[2]/12.0;
2681  Subsonic_Engine_Box[3] = Subsonic_Engine_Box[3]/12.0;
2682  Subsonic_Engine_Box[4] = Subsonic_Engine_Box[4]/12.0;
2683  Subsonic_Engine_Box[5] = Subsonic_Engine_Box[5]/12.0;
2684 
2685  for (iMarker = 0; iMarker < nMarker_ActDisk_Inlet; iMarker++) {
2686  for (iDim = 0; iDim < val_nDim; iDim++)
2687  ActDisk_Origin[iMarker][iDim] = ActDisk_Origin[iMarker][iDim]/12.0;
2688  ActDisk_RootRadius[iMarker] = ActDisk_RootRadius[iMarker]/12.0;
2689  ActDisk_TipRadius[iMarker] = ActDisk_TipRadius[iMarker]/12.0;
2690  }
2691 
2692  }
2693 
2694  if (DirectDiff != NO_DERIVATIVE){
2695 #if !defined COMPLEX_TYPE && !defined ADOLC_FORWARD_TYPE && !defined CODI_FORWARD_TYPE
2696  if (Kind_SU2 == SU2_CFD){
2697  cout << "SU2_CFD: Config option DIRECT_DIFF= YES requires AD or complex support!" << endl;
2698  cout << "Please use SU2_CFD_DIRECTDIFF (configuration/compilation is done using the preconfigure.py script)." << endl;
2699  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
2700  }
2701 #endif
2702  /*--- Initialize the derivative values ---*/
2703  switch (DirectDiff) {
2704  case D_MACH:
2705  SU2_TYPE::SetDerivative(Mach, 1.0);
2706  break;
2707  case D_AOA:
2708  SU2_TYPE::SetDerivative(AoA, 1.0);
2709  break;
2710  case D_SIDESLIP:
2711  SU2_TYPE::SetDerivative(AoS, 1.0);
2712  break;
2713  case D_REYNOLDS:
2714  SU2_TYPE::SetDerivative(Reynolds, 1.0);
2715  break;
2716  case D_TURB2LAM:
2717  SU2_TYPE::SetDerivative(Turb2LamViscRatio_FreeStream, 1.0);
2718  break;
2719  default:
2720  /*--- All other cases are handled in the specific solver ---*/
2721  break;
2722  }
2723  }
2724 
2725 #if defined CODI_REVERSE_TYPE
2726  AD_Mode = YES;
2727 #else
2728  if (AD_Mode == YES){
2729  cout << "AUTO_DIFF=YES requires Automatic Differentiation support." << endl;
2730  cout << "Please use correct executables (configuration/compilation is done using the preconfigure.py script)." << endl;
2731  }
2732 #endif
2733 
2734  if (DiscreteAdjoint){
2735 #if !defined ADOLC_REVERSE_TYPE && !defined CODI_REVERSE_TYPE
2736  if (Kind_SU2 == SU2_CFD){
2737  cout << "SU2_CFD: Config option MATH_PROBLEM= DISCRETE_ADJOINT requires AD support!" << endl;
2738  cout << "Please use SU2_CFD_AD (configuration/compilation is done using the preconfigure.py script)." << endl;
2739  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
2740  }
2741 #endif
2742 
2743  /*--- Disable writing of limiters if enabled ---*/
2744  Wrt_Limiters = false;
2745 
2746  if (Unsteady_Simulation){
2747 
2748  Restart_Flow = false;
2749 
2750  if (Grid_Movement){
2751  cout << "Dynamic mesh movement currently not supported for the discrete adjoint solver." << endl;
2752  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
2753  }
2754 
2755  /* --- If the averaging interval is not set, we average over all time-steps ---*/
2756 
2757  if (Iter_Avg_Objective == 0.0){
2758  Iter_Avg_Objective = nExtIter;
2759  }
2760  }
2761 
2762  switch(Kind_Solver){
2763  case EULER:
2764  Kind_Solver = DISC_ADJ_EULER;
2765  break;
2766  case RANS:
2767  Kind_Solver = DISC_ADJ_RANS;
2768  Frozen_Visc = false;
2769  break;
2770  case NAVIER_STOKES:
2771  Kind_Solver = DISC_ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES;
2772  break;
2773  default:
2774  break;
2775  }
2776  }
2777 
2778  /*--- Check for 2nd order w/ limiting for JST and correct ---*/
2779 
2780  if ((Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow == SPACE_CENTERED) && (Kind_Centered_Flow == JST) && (SpatialOrder_Flow == SECOND_ORDER_LIMITER))
2781  SpatialOrder_Flow = SECOND_ORDER;
2782 
2783  if ((Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow == SPACE_CENTERED) && (Kind_Centered_AdjFlow == JST) && (SpatialOrder_AdjFlow == SECOND_ORDER_LIMITER))
2784  SpatialOrder_AdjFlow = SECOND_ORDER;
2785 
2786  delete [] tmp_smooth;
2787 
2788 }
2789 
2790 void CConfig::SetMarkers(unsigned short val_software) {
2791 
2792  unsigned short iMarker_All, iMarker_CfgFile, iMarker_Euler, iMarker_Custom,
2793  iMarker_FarField, iMarker_SymWall, iMarker_Pressure, iMarker_PerBound,
2794  iMarker_NearFieldBound, iMarker_InterfaceBound, iMarker_Dirichlet,
2795  iMarker_Inlet, iMarker_Riemann, iMarker_NRBC, iMarker_Outlet, iMarker_Isothermal,
2796  iMarker_HeatFlux, iMarker_EngineInflow, iMarker_EngineBleed, iMarker_EngineExhaust,
2797  iMarker_Displacement, iMarker_Load, iMarker_FlowLoad, iMarker_Neumann,
2798  iMarker_Monitoring, iMarker_Designing, iMarker_GeoEval, iMarker_Plotting,
2799  iMarker_DV, iMarker_Moving, iMarker_Supersonic_Inlet, iMarker_Supersonic_Outlet,
2800  iMarker_Clamped, iMarker_FSIinterface, iMarker_Load_Dir, iMarker_Load_Sine,
2801  iMarker_ActDisk_Inlet, iMarker_ActDisk_Outlet, iMarker_Out_1D;
2802 
2803  int size = SINGLE_NODE;
2804 
2805 #ifdef HAVE_MPI
2806  if (val_software != SU2_MSH)
2807  MPI_Comm_size(MPI_COMM_WORLD, &size);
2808 #endif
2809 
2810  /*--- Compute the total number of markers in the config file ---*/
2811 
2812  nMarker_CfgFile = nMarker_Euler + nMarker_FarField + nMarker_SymWall +
2813  nMarker_Pressure + nMarker_PerBound + nMarker_NearFieldBound +
2814  nMarker_InterfaceBound + nMarker_Dirichlet + nMarker_Neumann + nMarker_Inlet + nMarker_Riemann +
2815  nMarker_NRBC + nMarker_Outlet + nMarker_Isothermal + nMarker_HeatFlux +
2816  nMarker_EngineInflow + nMarker_EngineBleed + nMarker_EngineExhaust +
2817  nMarker_Supersonic_Inlet + nMarker_Supersonic_Outlet + nMarker_Displacement + nMarker_Load +
2818  nMarker_FlowLoad + nMarker_Custom +
2819  nMarker_Clamped + nMarker_Load_Sine + nMarker_Load_Dir +
2820  nMarker_ActDisk_Inlet + nMarker_ActDisk_Outlet + nMarker_Out_1D;
2821 
2822  /*--- Add the possible send/receive domains ---*/
2823 
2824  nMarker_Max = nMarker_CfgFile + 2*size;
2825 
2826  /*--- Basic dimensionalization of the markers (worst scenario) ---*/
2827 
2828  nMarker_All = nMarker_Max;
2829 
2830  /*--- Allocate the memory (markers in each domain) ---*/
2831 
2832  Marker_All_TagBound = new string[nMarker_All]; // Store the tag that correspond with each marker.
2833  Marker_All_SendRecv = new short[nMarker_All]; // +#domain (send), -#domain (receive).
2834  Marker_All_KindBC = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store the kind of boundary condition.
2835  Marker_All_Monitoring = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary should be monitored.
2836  Marker_All_Designing = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary should be designed.
2837  Marker_All_Plotting = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary should be plotted.
2838  Marker_All_FSIinterface = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary is in the FSI interface.
2839  Marker_All_GeoEval = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary should be geometry evaluation.
2840  Marker_All_DV = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary should be affected by design variables.
2841  Marker_All_Moving = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary should be in motion.
2842  Marker_All_PerBound = new short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary belongs to a periodic boundary.
2843  Marker_All_Out_1D = new unsigned short[nMarker_All]; // Store whether the boundary belongs to a 1-d output boundary.
2844 
2845  for (iMarker_All = 0; iMarker_All < nMarker_All; iMarker_All++) {
2846  Marker_All_TagBound[iMarker_All] = "SEND_RECEIVE";
2847  Marker_All_SendRecv[iMarker_All] = 0;
2848  Marker_All_KindBC[iMarker_All] = 0;
2849  Marker_All_Monitoring[iMarker_All] = 0;
2850  Marker_All_GeoEval[iMarker_All] = 0;
2851  Marker_All_Designing[iMarker_All] = 0;
2852  Marker_All_Plotting[iMarker_All] = 0;
2853  Marker_All_FSIinterface[iMarker_All] = 0;
2854  Marker_All_DV[iMarker_All] = 0;
2855  Marker_All_Moving[iMarker_All] = 0;
2856  Marker_All_PerBound[iMarker_All] = 0;
2857  Marker_All_Out_1D[iMarker_All] = 0;
2858  }
2859

2861

2863  Marker_CfgFile_KindBC = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];
2864  Marker_CfgFile_Monitoring = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];
2865  Marker_CfgFile_Designing = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];
2866  Marker_CfgFile_Plotting = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];
2867  Marker_CfgFile_GeoEval = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];

2869  Marker_CfgFile_DV = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];

2871  Marker_CfgFile_PerBound = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];
2872  Marker_CfgFile_Out_1D = new unsigned short[nMarker_CfgFile];
2873 
2874  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++) {
2875  Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] = "SEND_RECEIVE";
2876  Marker_CfgFile_KindBC[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;
2877  Marker_CfgFile_Monitoring[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;
2878  Marker_CfgFile_GeoEval[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;
2879  Marker_CfgFile_Designing[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;
2880  Marker_CfgFile_Plotting[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;
2881  Marker_CfgFile_FSIinterface[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;
2882  Marker_CfgFile_DV[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;
2883  Marker_CfgFile_Moving[iMarker_CfgFile] = 0;

2893  Marker_CfgFile_KindBC[iMarker_CfgFile] = EULER_WALL;

2899  Marker_CfgFile_KindBC[iMarker_CfgFile] = FAR_FIELD;
2900  iMarker_CfgFile++;
2901  }

4409 bool CConfig::TokenizeString(string & str, string & option_name,
4410  vector<string> & option_value) {
4411  const string delimiters(" ()[]{}:,\t\n\v\f\r");
4412  // check for comments or empty string
4413  string::size_type pos, last_pos;
4414  pos = str.find_first_of("%");
4415  if ( (str.length() == 0) || (pos == 0) ) {
4416  // str is empty or a comment line, so no option here
4417  return false;
4418  }
4419  if (pos != string::npos) {
4420  // remove comment at end if necessary
4421  str.erase(pos);
4422  }
4423 
4424  // look for line composed on only delimiters (usually whitespace)
4425  pos = str.find_first_not_of(delimiters);
4426  if (pos == string::npos) {
4427  return false;
4428  }
4429 
4430  // find the equals sign and split string
4431  string name_part, value_part;
4432  pos = str.find("=");
4433  if (pos == string::npos) {
4434  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
4435  << "line in the configuration file with no \"=\" sign."
4436  << endl;
4437  cout << "Look for: " << str << endl;
4438  cout << "str.length() = " << str.length() << endl;
4439  throw(-1);
4440  }
4441  name_part = str.substr(0, pos);
4442  value_part = str.substr(pos+1, string::npos);
4443  //cout << "name_part = |" << name_part << "|" << endl;
4444  //cout << "value_part = |" << value_part << "|" << endl;
4445 
4446  // the first_part should consist of one string with no interior delimiters
4447  last_pos = name_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, 0);
4448  pos = name_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
4449  if ( (name_part.length() == 0) || (last_pos == string::npos) ) {
4450  cerr << "Error in CConfig::TokenizeString(): "
4451  << "line in the configuration file with no name before the \"=\" sign."
4452  << endl;
4453  throw(-1);
4454  }
4455  if (pos == string::npos) pos = name_part.length();
4456  option_name = name_part.substr(last_pos, pos - last_pos);
4457  last_pos = name_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, pos);
4458  if (last_pos != string::npos) {
4459  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
4460  << "two or more options before an \"=\" sign in the configuration file."
4461  << endl;
4462  throw(-1);
4463  }
4464  StringToUpperCase(option_name);
4465 
4466  //cout << "option_name = |" << option_name << "|" << endl;
4467  //cout << "pos = " << pos << ": last_pos = " << last_pos << endl;
4468 
4469  // now fill the option value vector
4470  option_value.clear();
4471  last_pos = value_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, 0);
4472  pos = value_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
4473  while (string::npos != pos || string::npos != last_pos) {
4474  // add token to the vector<string>
4475  option_value.push_back(value_part.substr(last_pos, pos - last_pos));
4476  // skip delimiters
4477  last_pos = value_part.find_first_not_of(delimiters, pos);
4478  // find next "non-delimiter"
4479  pos = value_part.find_first_of(delimiters, last_pos);
4480  }
4481  if (option_value.size() == 0) {
4482  cerr << "Error in TokenizeString(): "
4483  << "option " << option_name << " in configuration file with no value assigned."
4484  << endl;
4485  throw(-1);
4486  }
4487 
4488 #if 0
4489  cout << "option value(s) = ";
4490  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
4491  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
4492  cout << endl;
4493 #endif
4494 
4495  // look for ';' DV delimiters attached to values
4496  vector<string>::iterator it;
4497  it = option_value.begin();
4498  while (it != option_value.end()) {
4499  if (it->compare(";") == 0) {
4500  it++;
4501  continue;
4502  }
4503 
4504  pos = it->find(';');
4505  if (pos != string::npos) {
4506  string before_semi = it->substr(0, pos);
4507  string after_semi= it->substr(pos+1, string::npos);
4508  if (before_semi.empty()) {
4509  *it = ";";
4510  it++;
4511  option_value.insert(it, after_semi);
4512  } else {
4513  *it = before_semi;
4514  it++;
4515  vector<string> to_insert;
4516  to_insert.push_back(";");
4517  if (!after_semi.empty())
4518  to_insert.push_back(after_semi);
4519  option_value.insert(it, to_insert.begin(), to_insert.end());
4520  }
4521  it = option_value.begin(); // go back to beginning; not efficient
4522  continue;
4523  } else {
4524  it++;
4525  }
4526  }
4527 #if 0
4528  cout << "option value(s) = ";
4529  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
4530  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
4531  cout << endl;
4532 #endif
4533  // remove any consecutive ";"
4534  it = option_value.begin();
4535  bool semi_at_prev = false;
4536  while (it != option_value.end()) {
4537  if (semi_at_prev) {
4538  if (it->compare(";") == 0) {
4539  option_value.erase(it);
4540  it = option_value.begin();
4541  semi_at_prev = false;
4542  continue;
4543  }
4544  }
4545  if (it->compare(";") == 0) {
4546  semi_at_prev = true;
4547  } else {
4548  semi_at_prev = false;
4549  }
4550  it++;
4551  }
4552 
4553 #if 0
4554  cout << "option value(s) = ";
4555  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < option_value.size(); i++)
4556  cout << option_value[i] << " ";
4557  cout << endl;
4558 #endif
4559  return true;
4560 }
4561 
4562 unsigned short CConfig::GetMarker_CfgFile_TagBound(string val_marker) {
4563 
4564  unsigned short iMarker_CfgFile;
4565 
4566  for (iMarker_CfgFile = 0; iMarker_CfgFile < nMarker_CfgFile; iMarker_CfgFile++)
4567  if (Marker_CfgFile_TagBound[iMarker_CfgFile] == val_marker)
4568  return iMarker_CfgFile;
4569 
4570  cout <<"The configuration file doesn't have any definition for marker "<< val_marker <<"!!" << endl;
4571  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
4572 
4573 }

4577 }

4829 string CConfig::GetUnsteady_FileName(string val_filename, int val_iter) {
4830 
4831  string UnstExt, UnstFilename = val_filename;
4832  char buffer[50];
4833 
4834  /*--- Check that a positive value iteration is requested (for now). ---*/
4835 
4836  if (val_iter < 0) {
4837  cout << "Requesting a negative iteration number for the restart file!!" << endl;
4838  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
4839  }
4840 
4841  /*--- Append iteration number for unsteady cases ---*/
4842  if ((Wrt_Unsteady) || (Unsteady_Simulation == TIME_SPECTRAL) || (Wrt_Dynamic)) {
4843  unsigned short lastindex = UnstFilename.find_last_of(".");
4844  UnstFilename = UnstFilename.substr(0, lastindex);
4845  if ((val_iter >= 0) && (val_iter < 10)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0000%d.dat", val_iter);
4846  if ((val_iter >= 10) && (val_iter < 100)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_000%d.dat", val_iter);
4847  if ((val_iter >= 100) && (val_iter < 1000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_00%d.dat", val_iter);
4848  if ((val_iter >= 1000) && (val_iter < 10000)) SPRINTF (buffer, "_0%d.dat", val_iter);
4849  if (val_iter >= 10000) SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d.dat", val_iter);
4850  string UnstExt = string(buffer);
4851  UnstFilename.append(UnstExt);
4852  }
4853 
4854  return UnstFilename;
4855 }
4856 
4857 string CConfig::GetMultizone_FileName(string val_filename, int val_iZone) {
4858 
4859  string multizone_filename = val_filename;
4860  char buffer[50];
4861 
4862  if (GetnZone() > 1){
4863  unsigned short lastindex = multizone_filename.find_last_of(".");
4864  multizone_filename = multizone_filename.substr(0, lastindex);
4865  SPRINTF (buffer, "_%d.dat", SU2_TYPE::Int(val_iZone));
4866  multizone_filename.append(string(buffer));
4867  }
4868 
4869  return multizone_filename;
4870 }

4872 string CConfig::GetObjFunc_Extension(string val_filename) {
4873 
4874  string AdjExt, Filename = val_filename;
4875 
4876  if (ContinuousAdjoint || DiscreteAdjoint) {
4877 
4878  /*--- Remove filename extension (.dat) ---*/
4879  unsigned short lastindex = Filename.find_last_of(".");
4880  Filename = Filename.substr(0, lastindex);
4881 
4882  switch (Kind_ObjFunc) {
4883  case DRAG_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cd"; break;
4884  case LIFT_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cl"; break;
4885  case SIDEFORCE_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_csf"; break;
4886  case INVERSE_DESIGN_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_invpress"; break;
4887  case INVERSE_DESIGN_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_invheat"; break;
4888  case MOMENT_X_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmx"; break;
4889  case MOMENT_Y_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmy"; break;
4890  case MOMENT_Z_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cmz"; break;
4891  case EFFICIENCY: AdjExt = "_eff"; break;
4892  case EQUIVALENT_AREA: AdjExt = "_ea"; break;
4893  case NEARFIELD_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_nfp"; break;
4894  case FORCE_X_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfx"; break;
4895  case FORCE_Y_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfy"; break;
4896  case FORCE_Z_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cfz"; break;
4897  case THRUST_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_ct"; break;
4898  case TORQUE_COEFFICIENT: AdjExt = "_cq"; break;
4899  case TOTAL_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_totheat"; break;
4900  case MAXIMUM_HEATFLUX: AdjExt = "_maxheat"; break;
4901  case FIGURE_OF_MERIT: AdjExt = "_merit"; break;
4902  case FREE_SURFACE: AdjExt = "_fs"; break;
4903  case AVG_TOTAL_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_pt"; break;
4904  case AVG_OUTLET_PRESSURE: AdjExt = "_pe"; break;
4905  case MASS_FLOW_RATE: AdjExt = "_mfr"; break;
4906  case OUTFLOW_GENERALIZED: AdjExt = "_chn"; break;
4907  }
4908  Filename.append(AdjExt);
4909 
4910  /*--- Lastly, add the .dat extension ---*/
4911  Filename.append(".dat");
4912 
4913  }
4914 
4915  return Filename;
4916 }

4948 void CConfig::SetGlobalParam(unsigned short val_solver,
4949  unsigned short val_system,
4950  unsigned long val_extiter) {
4951 
4952  /*--- Set the simulation global time ---*/
4953  Current_UnstTime = static_cast<su2double>(val_extiter)*Delta_UnstTime;
4954  Current_UnstTimeND = static_cast<su2double>(val_extiter)*Delta_UnstTimeND;
4955 
4956  /*--- Set the solver methods ---*/
4957  switch (val_solver) {
4958  case EULER:
4959  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
4960  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
4961  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
4962  SpatialOrder_Flow);
4963  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
4964  }
4965  break;
4966  case NAVIER_STOKES:
4967  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
4968  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
4969  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
4970  SpatialOrder_Flow);
4971  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
4972  }
4973  break;
4974  case RANS:
4975  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
4976  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
4977  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
4978  SpatialOrder_Flow);
4979  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
4980  }
4981  if (val_system == RUNTIME_TURB_SYS) {
4982  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb, Kind_Centered_Turb,
4983  Kind_Upwind_Turb, Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb,
4984  SpatialOrder_Turb);
4985  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Turb);
4986  }
4987  if (val_system == RUNTIME_TRANS_SYS) {
4988  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb, Kind_Centered_Turb,
4989  Kind_Upwind_Turb, Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb,
4990  SpatialOrder_Turb);
4991  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Turb);
4992  }
4993  break;
4994  case ADJ_EULER:
4995  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
4996  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
4997  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
4998  SpatialOrder_Flow);
4999  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
5000  }
5001  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJFLOW_SYS) {
5002  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjFlow, Kind_Centered_AdjFlow,
5003  Kind_Upwind_AdjFlow, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjFlow,
5004  SpatialOrder_AdjFlow);
5005  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjFlow);
5006  }
5007  break;
5008  case ADJ_NAVIER_STOKES:
5009  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
5010  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
5011  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
5012  SpatialOrder_Flow);

5014  }
5015  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJFLOW_SYS) {

5017  Kind_Upwind_AdjFlow, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjFlow,
5018  SpatialOrder_AdjFlow);
5019  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjFlow);
5020  }
5021  break;
5022  case ADJ_RANS:
5023  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FLOW_SYS) {
5024  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Flow, Kind_Centered_Flow,
5025  Kind_Upwind_Flow, Kind_SlopeLimit_Flow,
5026  SpatialOrder_Flow);
5027  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Flow);
5028  }
5029  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJFLOW_SYS) {

5033  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjFlow);
5034  }

5036  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_Turb, Kind_Centered_Turb,
5037  Kind_Upwind_Turb, Kind_SlopeLimit_Turb,
5038  SpatialOrder_Turb);
5039  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Turb);
5040  }
5041  if (val_system == RUNTIME_ADJTURB_SYS) {
5042  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(Kind_ConvNumScheme_AdjTurb, Kind_Centered_AdjTurb,
5043  Kind_Upwind_AdjTurb, Kind_SlopeLimit_AdjTurb,
5044  SpatialOrder_AdjTurb);
5045  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_AdjTurb);
5046  }
5047  break;
5048  case POISSON_EQUATION:
5049  if (val_system == RUNTIME_POISSON_SYS) {
5050  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE);
5051  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Poisson);
5052  }
5053  break;
5054  case WAVE_EQUATION:
5055  if (val_system == RUNTIME_WAVE_SYS) {
5056  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE);
5057  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Wave);
5058  }
5059  break;
5060  case HEAT_EQUATION:
5061  if (val_system == RUNTIME_HEAT_SYS) {
5062  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE);
5063  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_Heat);
5064  }
5065  break;
5066  case FEM_ELASTICITY:
5067 
5068  Current_DynTime = static_cast<su2double>(val_extiter)*Delta_DynTime;
5069 
5070  if (val_system == RUNTIME_FEA_SYS) {
5071  SetKind_ConvNumScheme(NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE, NONE);
5072  SetKind_TimeIntScheme(Kind_TimeIntScheme_FEA);
5073  }
5074  break;
5075  }
5076 }

5099 unsigned short CConfig::GetMarker_Periodic_Donor(string val_marker) {
5100  unsigned short iMarker_PerBound, jMarker_PerBound, kMarker_All;
5101 
5102  /*--- Find the marker for this periodic boundary. ---*/
5103  for (iMarker_PerBound = 0; iMarker_PerBound < nMarker_PerBound; iMarker_PerBound++)
5104  if (Marker_PerBound[iMarker_PerBound] == val_marker) break;
5105 
5106  /*--- Find corresponding donor. ---*/
5107  for (jMarker_PerBound = 0; jMarker_PerBound < nMarker_PerBound; jMarker_PerBound++)
5108  if (Marker_PerBound[jMarker_PerBound] == Marker_PerDonor[iMarker_PerBound]) break;
5109 
5110  /*--- Find and return global marker index for donor boundary. ---*/
5111  for (kMarker_All = 0; kMarker_All < nMarker_CfgFile; kMarker_All++)
5112  if (Marker_PerBound[jMarker_PerBound] == Marker_All_TagBound[kMarker_All]) break;
5113 
5114  return kMarker_All;
5115 }

5497  return Load_Sine_Dir[iMarker_Load_Sine];
5498 }
5499 
5500 su2double CConfig::GetFlowLoad_Value(string val_marker) {
5501  unsigned short iMarker_FlowLoad;
5502  for (iMarker_FlowLoad = 0; iMarker_FlowLoad < nMarker_FlowLoad; iMarker_FlowLoad++)
5503  if (Marker_FlowLoad[iMarker_FlowLoad] == val_marker) break;
5504  return FlowLoad_Value[iMarker_FlowLoad];
5505 }
5506 
5507 void CConfig::SetSpline(vector<su2double> &x, vector<su2double> &y, unsigned long n, su2double yp1, su2double ypn, vector<su2double> &y2) {
5508  unsigned long i, k;
5509  su2double p, qn, sig, un, *u;
5510 
5511  u = new su2double [n];
5512 
5513  if (yp1 > 0.99e30) // The lower boundary condition is set either to be "nat
5514  y2[0]=u[0]=0.0; // -ural"
5515  else { // or else to have a specified first derivative.
5516  y2[0] = -0.5;
5517  u[0]=(3.0/(x[1]-x[0]))*((y[1]-y[0])/(x[1]-x[0])-yp1);
5518  }
5519 
5520  for (i=2; i<=n-1; i++) { // This is the decomposition loop of the tridiagonal al-
5521  sig=(x[i-1]-x[i-2])/(x[i]-x[i-2]); // gorithm. y2 and u are used for tem-
5522  p=sig*y2[i-2]+2.0; // porary storage of the decomposed
5523  y2[i-1]=(sig-1.0)/p; // factors.
5524  u[i-1]=(y[i]-y[i-1])/(x[i]-x[i-1]) - (y[i-1]-y[i-2])/(x[i-1]-x[i-2]);
5525  u[i-1]=(6.0*u[i-1]/(x[i]-x[i-2])-sig*u[i-2])/p;
5526  }
5527 
5528  if (ypn > 0.99e30) // The upper boundary condition is set either to be
5529  qn=un=0.0; // "natural"
5530  else { // or else to have a specified first derivative.
5531  qn=0.5;
5532  un=(3.0/(x[n-1]-x[n-2]))*(ypn-(y[n-1]-y[n-2])/(x[n-1]-x[n-2]));
5533  }
5534  y2[n-1]=(un-qn*u[n-2])/(qn*y2[n-2]+1.0);
5535  for (k=n-1; k>=1; k--) // This is the backsubstitution loop of the tridiagonal
5536  y2[k-1]=y2[k-1]*y2[k]+u[k-1]; // algorithm.
5537 
5538  delete[] u;
5539 
5540 }
5541 
5542 su2double CConfig::GetSpline(vector<su2double>&xa, vector<su2double>&ya, vector<su2double>&y2a, unsigned long n, su2double x) {
5543  unsigned long klo, khi, k;
5544  su2double h, b, a, y;
5545 
5546  klo=1; // We will find the right place in the table by means of
5547  khi=n; // bisection. This is optimal if sequential calls to this
5548  while (khi-klo > 1) { // routine are at random values of x. If sequential calls
5549  k=(khi+klo) >> 1; // are in order, and closely spaced, one would do better
5550  if (xa[k-1] > x) khi=k; // to store previous values of klo and khi and test if
5551  else klo=k; // they remain appropriate on the next call.
5552  } // klo and khi now bracket the input value of x
5553  h=xa[khi-1]-xa[klo-1];
5554  if (h == 0.0) cout << "Bad xa input to routine splint" << endl; // The xas must be dis-
5555  a=(xa[khi-1]-x)/h; // tinct.
5556  b=(x-xa[klo-1])/h; // Cubic spline polynomial is now evaluated.
5557  y=a*ya[klo-1]+b*ya[khi-1]+((a*a*a-a)*y2a[klo-1]+(b*b*b-b)*y2a[khi-1])*(h*h)/6.0;
5558 
5559  return y;
5560 }

CConfig::SetSpline
void SetSpline(vector< su2double > &x, vector< su2double > &y, unsigned long n, su2double yp1, su2double ypn, vector< su2double > &y2)
Given arrays x[1..n] and y[1..n] containing a tabulated function, i.e., yi = f(xi), with x1 < x2 < . . . < xN , and given values yp1 and ypn for the first derivative of the interpolating function at points 1 and n, respectively, this routine returns an array y2[1..n] that contains the second derivatives of the interpolating function at the tabulated points xi. If yp1 and/or ypn are equal to 1 1030 or larger, the routine is signaled to set the corresponding boundary condition for a natural spline, with zero second derivative on that boundary. Numerical Recipes: The Art of Scientific Computing, Third Edition in C++.
